image_analysis.description: A photograph of a bidet located in a small alcove. The lower half of the walls and the floor are covered in white marble with grey veining. A black trim separates the marble from the upper wall, which is painted a light beige or cream color. On the left wall, there is a chrome towel rack holding two white towels. On the back wall, above the bidet, there is a small chrome soap dish. The bidet itself is white porcelain with chrome fixtures. To the right, a portion of a doorway or curtain is visible with a red fabric hanging.
